00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:18.000
It's important that you check your guitar tuning before the performance...

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:20.000
At least a while before.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:28.000
Also when you have your set ready for your performance

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Because, it use to happen, when you Carrie your stuff...

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:38.000
Your guitar gets out of tune.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:42.000
Or it can happen when you have an outside concert

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:44.000
In a public space

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:55.000
The instrument, that you brought tuned inside the case, it can happen that it gets out of tune because of temperature changes.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:05.000
So, when you have your set ready to start your performance, it's good that you check again the tuning

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:11.000
Otherwise, you could play your first song out of tune, and it's not good.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:19.000
